author: The Virginian-Pilot
title: Field hockey | Va. Wesleyan posts senior day shutout
text:
VIRGINIA BEACH Valentina Jones had a goal and an assist to pace Virginia Wesleyan to a 2-0 ODAC victory over Eastern Mennonite on Senior Day.
Jones scored the first goal for the Marlins (6-11, 2-3) off an assist from Morgan Lee (Bayside High).
Jones then assisted on Grassfield grad Melissa Rideout's goal at 66:55.
Skye Swain made nine saves in posting the shutout.
The Marlins play their final home game of the regular season against Washington and Lee at 3:30 p.m. Tuesday.
